 href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-updates-its-mac-book-pros-with-m-2-pro-and-max-chips-143848558.html">1 月份才上市的</a>M2 Max 相比，高端笔记本电脑芯片 M3 Max 将拥有四个更多的高性能 CPU 核心和至少两个额外的图形核心。</p><p>据报道，该公司正在测试新的 iMac、13 英寸 MacBook Pro、13 英寸和 15 英寸 MacBook Air 和 Mac mini，所有产品都运行 M3 芯片，预计在未来 12 个月内测试。配备 M3 Pro 和 M3 Max 芯片的更新版 14 英寸和 16 英寸 MacBook Pro 型号可能要到 2024 年才会上市。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该公司可能会采取积极的 Mac 发布计划，因为其台式机和笔记本电脑产品线在<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/report-apple-sold-a-record-number-of-mac-books-last-quarter-091233817.html">大流行时代的繁荣</a>后难以重新获得销售基础。尽管它在 6 月份推出了<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-macbook-air-15-inch-review-a-bigger-screen-makes-a-surprising-difference-130033172.html">15 英寸 MacBook Air</a> ，并在 1 月份推出了新款<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-macbook-pro-14-inch-review-2023-m2-pro-max-140048268.html">MacBook Pro</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mac-mini-review-m2-pro-2023-140052205.html">Mac mini</a> ，但今年秋天我们可能会看到更多新的 Mac 硬件。 （该公司在上周的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-services-are-making-more-cash-than-ever-but-revenue-shrank-for-the-third-quarter-in-a-row-205545482.html">财报电话会议</a>上暗示，新的 Mac 电脑要到 9 月底结束的第四财季之后才会上市。） 据<em>彭博社</em>报道，苹果确实计划在 10 月份推出产品。</p><p>据报道，基础 M3 芯片将使用与 M2 相同的配置：8 个处理器核心和最多 10 个图形核心。然而，M3 Pro 将从 12 个 CPU 核心和 18 个图形核心开始，测试日志表明 M3 Max 将包括 16 个 CPU 核心和 40 个图形核心。当然，苹果可能正在测试核心数量选项的多种变体，但我们尚不知道哪些版本将提供给消费者。</p><p>长期以来一直有传言称，M3 芯片将转向<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/intel-and-apple-expected-to-debut-3-nm-processors-next-year-100632556.html">台积电即将推出的 3 纳米工艺，与 M2 中使用的 5 纳米工艺相比，预期性能和效率将得到</a>改善。人们还普遍预计苹果将在<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-set-to-feature-a-thinner-bezel-titanium-frame-and-usb-c-charging-094118389.html">即将推出的 iPhone 15 系列</a>中使用 3nm 工艺的 A17 芯片。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/apple-is-reportedly-testing-m3-chips-for-new-macs-arriving-this-fall-173457588.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apple-is-reportedly-testing-m3-chips-for-new-macs-arriving-this-fall-173457588.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 69d7aaa5-91d5-4cfa-8e47-c14f342672cb</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 17:34:57 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691516098</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T17:35:05+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="3233" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/460b8200-3610-11ee-a7d7-eda8ad2abcfd" width="4618"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3233" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/460b8200-3610-11ee-a7d7-eda8ad2abcfd" width="4618"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - Apple CEO Tim Cook stands in front of a display of new Apple MacBook Air computers with M2 processors, Monday, June 6, 2022, following the keynote presentation of Apple's World Wide Developer Conference on the campus of Apple's headquarters in Cupertino, Calif. Apple's foray into live sports took a big step forward Tuesday, June 14, 2022. Apple and Major League Soccer have announced a 10-year partnership on a streaming service that will allow fans to watch every game without local blackouts or restrictions. The service will be available exclusively through the Apple TV app beginning next year. (AP Photo/Noah Berger, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[MLS Apple]]></media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>